---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="sticker journaling tips">
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-primary transition-colors market-aware-link" data-href="/blog">← back to blog</a>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-6 mb-2">June 1, 2026</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-6">5 sticker journaling tips for beginners</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-sm text-gray-600 space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
      <p>stickers are one of the easiest ways to make your journal feel personal — no drawing skills required. here are five simple tips to get started.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">1. start with a theme</h2>
      <p>pick one mood for the page: cozy café, rainy day, or pastel dreams. choosing a theme first makes it easier to pick which sticker sheet to reach for.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">2. layer small accents</h2>
      <p>instead of filling the whole page, place a few stickers near your handwriting or photos. tiny accents often look more polished than a crowded spread.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">3. mix textures</h2>
      <p>combine washi tape, handwritten notes, and vinyl stickers. the contrast between matte paper and glossy sticker surfaces adds depth.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">4. leave white space</h2>
      <p>empty space is not wasted space. letting the page breathe keeps your journal readable and gives each sticker room to shine.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">5. keep a sticker stash</h2>
      <p>store your favorite sheets in a small pouch so you can journal on the go. a mini collection of go-to designs saves decision fatigue.</p>

      <p class="pt-4">happy journaling — and if you need fresh sheets, browse our <a href="/products" class="text-primary hover:underline market-aware-link" data-href="/products">sticker collection</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
